                    <span>Mr Roman is an extremely competent and clear writer. This book, whilst not as big as some, doesn't waste space with any padding, and boring repititious stuff you see in some texts.  
<br />Although there could have been a little more on interplay between Excel and the other Office objects, esp. Outlook, this book makes up for that with its clear, organised and logical presenatation.  
<br />
<br />I use it as a reference book, and seem to remember the content of it more clearly than I do with other comparable books! Why is this?  Mr Roman has a tidy turn of phrase, doesn't wafffle, but his explanations seem to sit well in how my mind works. I hope this will be the same for you. 
<br />
<br />  I recommend this book for those who may be beyond the beginner stage of learning VB(A). It also includes some handy utilities for users of Excel.
<br />
<br />Mr Roman  - well done.  Look forward to your next (high level?) Excel VBA book.</span>
                  
